title: Replies to supplementary questions raised by Finance Committee Members in examining the Estimates of Expenditure 2013-14
question_text: According to Reply Serial No. FSTB(Tsy)075, the Administration estimates that the demand for non-departmental quarters (NDQs) will diminish progressively. Has the Administration planed to demolish the vacant NDQs for building public rental housing and Home Ownership Scheme flats to meet the increasing demand for housing in the society?
reply_text: There are two main classes of government quarters, namely non-departmental quarters (NDQs) and departmental quarters (DQs), and the Civil Service Bureau and the concerned Heads of Department are responsible for their allocation respectively. The Administration has been reviewing the demand and supply of NDQs regularly and where feasible, will use the surplus NDQs as DQs, or put them up for letting or sale. Besides, the Administration will demolish quarters that are not habitable or hand over the surplus sites to the Lands Department for long-term development. For example, after taking over the ex-NDQ site at 8-12 Deep Water Bay Drive, Shouson Hill, the Lands Department sold the land by tender last year to increase the supply of private domestic units. In addition, the Government has used the following ex-DQ sites in recent years for constructing public housing: (1) Ex-Kwai Chung Police Married Quarters, Kwai Chung Road, Kwai Chung; (2) Ex-Shatin Police Married Quarters, Fung Shun Street, Sha Tin; (3) Ex-Shatin Fire Services Rank and File Quarters, Fung Shun Street, Sha Tin; and (4) Ex-Au Tau Departmental Quarters, Yau Shin Street, Yuen Long. Session 4 FSTB(Tsy) - Page 24 In general, the Planning Department will assess the redevelopment potential of vacant quarters sites for private or public housing to optimise land utilization, by taking into account relevant factors including the character of the locality, compatibility with the surrounding environment, transport and infrastructure capacity, etc. Name in block letters: Alan Siu Post Title: Government Property Administrator Date: 19.4.2013 Session 4 FSTB(Tsy) - Page 25
